An Act relative to roadway damage.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 26 of Chapter 90 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022
2 Official Edition, is hereby amended by inserting at the end thereof the following paragraph:- The
3 registrar shall issue a report to the Department of Transportation (DOT) on public roadway
4 damage resulting from an accident in which any person is killed or injured or in which there is
5 damage in excess of one thousand dollars to any one vehicle or other property. The report shall
6 be issued no more than thirty days after said accident.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon its passage.
